#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
build-ini-gui — interactive .ini composer for CAP analyses.

Acts as a middle-man between the user and CAP's configuration system. Knows
the package structure (which task classes exist, what keys they consume,
what reasonable defaults are), so the user gets to declare WHAT they want
to study and the GUI emits a complete, internally-consistent .ini.

  Run:
      ./analyses/builder/build-ini-gui
      ./install --build-ini       # equivalent

  Output:
      analyses/projects/<job-name>.ini

  Adding a new analysis preset:
      drop a Python file with a top-level PRESET in
      analyses/builder/presets/. The dropdown picks it up automatically.
"""
